        <h3>The Mark & Promotion Logic: Decoding Uniraj Marksheets</h3>
        <p>A frequent search regarding **raj university online marks 2024** is about the 'Passing Threshold'. For the 2024 cycle, Uniraj follows a strict state policy threshold:</p>
        <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
            <li><strong>Min Passing Marks</strong>: Students must secure a minimum of 36% marks in each subject (Theory and Practical separately) to be declared 'Passed'. For Honours, the threshold is typically 48-50%.</li>
            <li><strong>Due Paper Policy</strong>: Students failing in one or two subjects can promote to the next year provided they clear the 'Due' papers in the subsequent annual exam cycle.</li>
            <li><strong>POPS (Pass in Optional Subjects)</strong>: Marks of qualifying subjects like 'General Hindi', 'General English', and 'Environment' are not included in the main percentage but must be cleared to get the final degree.</li>
        <li><strong>Outcome</strong>: This ensures that Rajasthan graduates are academically resilient and prepared for the national-level 'Civil Services' and 'RAS' competition.</li>
        </ul>

